articles.description: USC's investigation into the college basketball bribery scandal found no institutional neglect by its program. Athletic director Lynn Swann said then-assistant coach Tony Bland "was operating outside [the] boundaries."
articles.headline: USC probe finds no institutional neglect; Tony Bland acted 'outside boundaries'

articles.description: Gary Chivichyan set career highs with eight 3-pointers and 25 points, Jared Stutzman had four 3s and 20 points, including the go-ahead jumper with 41 seconds left, and Idaho State beat Sacramento State 67-60 on Thursday night.
articles.headline: Idaho State hits 12 3s in 67-60 win over Sacramento State

articles.description: The Wildcats have owned the Big East, but recent losses have opened the door for the Musketeers to take the league, starting with Saturday's matchup.
articles.headline: Weekend lookahead: Xavier, Villanova battle for Big East supremacy

images.caption: Xavier can avenge its Jan. 10 loss to Villanova when the Wildcats visit on Saturday.
images.name: Tyrique Jones [576x324]

articles.description: In a league as competitive as the Big 12, opportunities abound for quality wins. The problem, as Texas and Oklahoma are learning in recent weeks, is winning those games. Will the Longhorns or Sooners end their losing streaks this weekend?
articles.headline: Bubble Watch: Struggling to survive in a rugged Big 12

images.caption: Texas wants to end its three-game losing streak on Saturday against Oklahoma.
images.name: Bamba_Mohamed 180213 [608x342]

images.caption: Deandre Ayton scores 25 points and grabs 16 rebounds as No. 17 Arizona holds off No. 25 Arizona State, 77-70.
images.name: Arizona completes season sweep of Arizona State

articles.description: Gregg Marshall yells and screams. That's how he gets his point across. But he also listens. Amid an up-and-down year at Wichita State, the man whom bigger programs are always chasing will listen again.
articles.headline: It's time for the almost-annual question: Can Wichita State keep Gregg Marshall?

images.caption: Gregg Marshall has had chances to leave Wichita State. Is this the time he actually bolts?
images.name: Gregg Marshall [1296x864]

images.caption: Wichita State fans are behind Gregg Marshall. That much is clear.
images.name: Gregg Marshall [608x342]

images.caption: Gregg Marshall does not mince words when he wants to get his point across.
images.name: Gregg Marshall [608x342]

articles.description: After being asked to not single out Arizona State players using his megaphone, an Arizona cheerleader continued to heckle and was ejected.

videos.description: Trae Young opens the game locked in from downtown, draining a 3-pointer after putting on a dribbling clinic.
videos.headline: Oklahoma's Young puts defender on skates

videos.description: Trae Young shows off his range by sinking a deep 3-pointer for the Sooners in the first half.
videos.headline: Oklahoma's Young drills deep 3

videos.description: Trae Young shakes TCU's defense and hits a 3-pointer for the game's first points.
videos.headline: Young mesmerizes defender, nails step-back 3 to start game

tracking.trackingName: NCB_One-Play (Young mesmerizes defender, nails stepback 3 to start game) 2018/01/13 ESHEET

videos.description: Trae Young's dad Rayford offers his opinion on his son's decision to stay in his home state of Oklahoma to play college ball.
videos.headline: Young's dad happy Trae stayed home

videos.description: Khadeem Lattin gets back on defense after a turnover and sends a shot attempt into the crowd for the Sooners.
videos.headline: Oklahoma's Lattin denies TCU

videos.description: Jamuni McNeace displays some grown man post moves, spinning his way to an impressive one-handed slam.
videos.headline: Oklahoma's McNeace goes to work in the paint

videos.description: Kouat Noi silences the crowd in Oklahoma by draining a 3-pointer from the corner for the Horned Frogs.
videos.headline: TCU'S Noi splashes home 3-pointer

videos.description: Trae Young drives to the basket and gets the flashy layup to fall in the second half for the Sooners.
videos.headline: Oklahoma's Young sinks acrobatic layup

videos.description: Trae Young paralyzes his defender with his dribbling ability and drains the 3-pointer to tie it late in the second half.
videos.headline: Oklahoma's Young sinks clutch 3

videos.description: Christian James gets the dish from Trae Young  and sinks  the clutch 3-pointer to give the Sooners the lead late in the second half.
videos.headline: Oklahoma's James knocks down 3 to take lead

videos.description: Jaylen Fisher drives right through the Oklahoma defense and lays it in with ease to send the game into overtime.
videos.headline: TCU's Fisher sends game to OT

videos.description: Trae Young sinks yet another 3-pointer for the Sooners, giving Oklahoma some breathing room late in OT.
videos.headline: Oklahoma's Young puts on a shooting clinic

videos.description: Oklahoma freshman Trae Young is very humble after dropping 43 points in a 102 -97 win over TCU.
videos.headline: Young has high praise for teammates

videos.description: Reid Gettys and Lowell Galindo break down Trae Young's 43-point performance as Oklahoma beats TCU in overtime.
videos.headline: Young too much for TCU

videos.description: Oklahoma's Trae Young leads No. 9 Oklahoma to a 102-97 overtime victory over No. 16 TCU with slick moves and long-range accuracy.
videos.headline: Young hangs 43 on TCU in dazzling performance
